The cause of the issue was yet another entity, which has a OneToMany relationship with the ExpectedBusinessTimestamp as SortedSet&lt;ExpectedBusinessTimestamp&gt; and annotated with @SortNatural. The SortedSet enforces the use of the Comparable-interface, which is why there was a compareTo method in the ExpectedBusinessTimestamp class in the first place.

Changing the SortedSet to a List and using @OrderBy annotation instead of @SortNatural has solved all issues.

    @OneToMany(mappedBy = &quot;expectedBusinessTimestampTemplate&quot;, orphanRemoval = true, cascade = CascadeType.ALL)
    @OrderBy(&quot;date asc, time asc&quot;)
    private List&lt;ExpectedBusinessTimestamp&gt; expectedBusinessTimestamps;

